# ── Playwright parity evidence (AAP §0.6.2) ────────────────────────────────
# The `e2e-react/artifacts/` tree is written to by Playwright and holds TWO very
# different kinds of files:
#   (a) DURABLE, human-reviewed parity evidence — the curated before/after
#       screenshots and videos that ARE the migration deliverable and MUST be
#       committed (baseline vs. react), plus each folder's README.md/.gitkeep.
#   (b) TRANSIENT per-run debris — Playwright's auto per-test screenshots
#       (`test-finished-*.png`, `test-failed-*.png`), per-test `video.webm`,
#       failure `trace.zip`, `error-context.md`, the HTML `report/`, and the
#       runner's `.last-run.json`. Playwright REGENERATES this on every run and
#       wipes each project's `outputDir` at the start of a run, so committing it
#       would both add churn and risk stale junk in version control.
#
# Issue 10 fix: the previous blanket `!e2e-react/artifacts/**` un-ignored the
# transient debris too. Instead, IGNORE the whole artifacts tree and RE-INCLUDE
# ONLY the curated evidence subfolders (`screenshots/`, `videos/`) and the docs.
# Git cannot re-include a path whose parent directory stays excluded, so every
# parent directory is re-included before its contents.
e2e-react/artifacts/**
!e2e-react/artifacts/
!e2e-react/artifacts/baseline/
!e2e-react/artifacts/react/
!e2e-react/artifacts/**/README.md
!e2e-react/artifacts/**/.gitkeep
!e2e-react/artifacts/baseline/screenshots/
!e2e-react/artifacts/baseline/screenshots/**
!e2e-react/artifacts/react/screenshots/
!e2e-react/artifacts/react/screenshots/**
!e2e-react/artifacts/baseline/videos/
!e2e-react/artifacts/baseline/videos/**
!e2e-react/artifacts/react/videos/
!e2e-react/artifacts/react/videos/**

# Jest coverage output (React migration test runner). Generated by `jest --coverage`
# (jest.config.js coverageDirectory = coverage/react); never committed.
/coverage/
